news.title: About 390 mixed-occupancy buildings in Nagpur, 139 declared unsafe in fire safety audit
news.para: Nagpur's mixed-use buildings pose significant fire hazards, with a recent audit revealing widespread safety norm violations. Over half of these structures lack essential fire safety measures, leading to urgent action by the Municipal Corporation to disconnect power and water to non-compliant establishments.

news.title: SC agrees to hear ED's plea against Bombay HC order declaring former Vasai-Virar civic body chief's arrest as illegal
news.para: The Supreme Court will hear the Enforcement Directorate's challenge to a Bombay High Court ruling. The High Court had declared the arrest of former Vasai-Virar civic body chief Anil Pawar in a money laundering case illegal. The ED had arrested Pawar on August 13. The case involves alleged illegal constructions and builders conniving with officials.

news.title: Extend Airport metro to new Gurugram, RWAs tell minister
news.para: RWA representatives met Union minister Rao Inderjit Singh, urging him to extend the Delhi Airport Metro line to new Gurgaon sectors along the Dwarka e-way. They also requested bus services for last-mile connectivity, highlighting the lack of public transport in rapidly urbanizing areas. Singh assured them he had taken up the matter at the central level.

news.title: YEIDA will build housing clusters for Heritage City
news.para: The Yamuna Expressway Industrial Development Authority will now develop residential and commercial clusters for the Rs 7,200-crore Heritage City project near Mathura-Vrindavan. A public-private partnership model will be adopted for religious, cultural, and tourism infrastructure. The project, spanning 753 acres, will feature a heritage-themed township and a 30km Yamuna riverfront.

news.title: Ghaziabad: Over 70 plots up for grabs in Raj Nagar Extension & Noornagar
news.para: Ghaziabad Development Authority has launched a residential plot scheme in Raj Nagar Extension and Noornagar, offering 77 land parcels for sale. Simultaneously, progress is being made on an industrial cum logistic park in Modinagar, with land acquisition underway for the 250-hectare project. This initiative aims to boost industrial development and improve traffic management.

news.title: Delhi: Signature View Apartments to be demolished manually due to its poor structure
news.para: Delhi Development Authority will demolish Signature View Apartments floor-by-floor due to poor structural integrity, opting against implosion. Demolition is imminent, with DDA finalizing an agency. Residents are urged to vacate fully, as a final notice has been issued, with the agency given four months for dismantling.

news.title: Cops join Karnataka-RERA crackdown on defaulting builders
news.para: Homebuyers welcome move, hope Rs 750 crore recovery prevents prolonged delays, restores confidence, encourages compliance, highlights government commitment, creates precedent for future enforcement

news.title: Bombay HC restores registration of housing society federation
news.para: The Bombay High Court reinstated a housing society federation's registration, deeming its de-registration order "unsustainable." The court found the appeal, filed seven years late, was based on false reasons for delay. Justice Amit Borkar emphasized that judicial discretion shouldn't reward falsehoods, restoring the original registration.

news.title: Fish drying land tagged slum ‘to favour builder’: Khar Kolis to Bombay HC
news.para: Two Koli community societies have moved the Bombay High Court challenging an SRA order declaring land used for fish drying as a slum rehabilitation area. They argue the order undermines their livelihood and is arbitrary, favouring a developer over their statutory rights and fundamental freedoms.

news.title: PNB Housing Finance net profit rises 23.83% in Q2 FY26
news.para: PNB Housing Finance reported a robust 23.83% year-on-year growth in net consolidated profit for Q2 FY26, reaching ₹581.59 crore. The company's total income also saw a 13.35% increase. PNB Housing Finance is focusing on accelerating retail growth and expanding its affordable and emerging markets segment footprint.

news.title: Delhi: Residents barred from complaining against flat quality, design of DDA's premium housing scheme
news.para: Delhi Development Authority's Towering Heights housing scheme in East Delhi will not accept complaints regarding flat defects. This premium housing project offers 1,026 flats starting at Rs 1.78 crore. Construction is expected to be ready by July 2026. Successful bidders will pay 75 percent at e-auction and the rest by possession.

news.title: Suraj Estate Developers' net profit up 3.96% in Q2 FY26
news.para: Suraj Estate Developers announced strong financial results for the quarter ending September 30, 2025. The company saw its net profit grow by 3.96 percent. Total income also experienced a significant increase of 32.65 percent. The board also approved a postal ballot to seek shareholder approval for the appointment of Ananta Singh Raghuvanshi as an independent director.

news.title: Mumbai: Original owners of Sanjan bungalow oppose sale
news.para: Original owners of a Sanjan bungalow are vehemently opposing its sale by the World Zoroastrian Organisation Trust Funds. The Davierwalla family sold the property at a below-market rate in 1997, stipulating it be used solely for Parsi-Irani community welfare.  Concerns are raised about commercial exploitation, with a community group offering to buy it to keep it within the fold.

news.title: Della Group eyes ₹700 crore revenue, ₹450 crore EBITDA by FY27
news.para: Della Group projects a significant revenue surge to ₹700 crore by FY27, driven by a new proprietary real estate model and expansion into integrated townships. This shift from its Lonavala resort operations, which generated ₹200 crore in FY25, aims to unlock higher value for partners through an end-to-end CDDMO framework.

news.title: Controversy erupts over Indore civic body property survey, mayor suspends drive till SOP is ready
news.para: A property tax survey by the Indore Municipal Corporation sparked a major controversy, leading to a standoff at a police station and multiple FIRs. High-level political intervention followed, with a cabinet minister calling for a resolution. The mayor has since halted the survey, promising a new Standard Operating Procedure and public appeal for property assessment corrections.

news.title: Shriram Properties to jointly develop row housing project in Yelahanka, Bengaluru
news.para: Shriram Properties has entered a joint development agreement for seven acres in North Bengaluru. This land will be used to develop row houses. The project has an estimated gross development value of ₹600 crore. The company is focusing on partnerships for growth. Yelahanka's infrastructure and proximity to a biodiversity park make it a prime location for premium homes.

news.title: Goa housing board gets nod for legal, IT wings
news.para: Goa's state cabinet has approved the establishment of a legal and IT cell within the Goa Housing Board (GHB), creating 11 new posts. This move aims to bolster the board's capacity to provide affordable housing and manage its operations. The GHB, a self-sustaining statutory body, will now enhance its legal and technological infrastructure.

news.title: Telangana: TRSCL to conduct e-auction of plots from October 28
news.para: Telangana Rajiv Swagruha Corporation Limited is holding an e-auction for open plots in Kurmalguda, Thorrur, and Bahadurpally from October 28-30. Plot sizes vary, with upset prices ranging from ₹20,000 to ₹30,000 per square yard. The auction will be conducted in multiple sessions across the three days.
